Delta State governor, Ifeanyi Okowa, and his wife, Edith, have both tested positive for COVID-19. Okowa made the disclosure on his Facebook page on Wednesday morning. He said, “My wife and I have tested positive for COVID-19. We are well and continuing with our isolation/medication. We thank you all for your continued prayers for us and our daughter.”  See Also






